# Hello Picnic v2 — Rules for AI coding agents

## Read this first
The contract for this project lives in docs/: REBUILD_PLAN.md (what & why),
ARCHITECTURE.md (how), DESIGN_PRINCIPLES.md (UI), TESTING.md (proof),
PROMPTS.md (AI behavior), AGENTS.md (who does what). Docs win over code.
If docs seem wrong: stop and report, don't improvise.

## Model roles (see docs/AGENTS.md)
- ARCHITECT = expensive tier (Claude Fable / Opus-class): owns docs, reviews all PRs,
  decides schema/security/API changes, writes crypto + AI-layer core.
- BUILDER = cheaper tier (Claude Sonnet-class autonomous; DeepSeek via owner-pasted
  prompts): implements exactly one work package per branch/PR.
- Builders NEVER: change DB schema outside their WP, touch src/server/auth/crypto.ts,
  edit docs/ to match their code, add dependencies not named in their WP without
  flagging it in the PR, or merge anything.
- Builder stuck twice on the same problem → escalate to architect, don't thrash.

## Scope discipline
- One work package (docs/workpackages/WP-XX-*.md) per branch `wp-XX-<slug>` per PR.
- Out-of-scope ideas go in the PR description under "Voorstellen", not in the diff.
- PR body = the WP's acceptance-criteria checklist (honestly ticked) + screenshots
  of changed screens (both 390px and 1280px viewports).

## Hard technical rules
- TypeScript strict; no `any` without an inline justification comment.
- Zod validation at every boundary: API input, LLM output, external API responses.
- LLM calls ONLY via src/server/integrations/ai (callStructured/callImage). Never
  parse model text with regex; never hardcode a model ID outside ai/models.ts.
- Pages → route handlers → services → integrations. Pages never import integrations.
- No secret (password, token, API key) may ever reach the client: not in DTOs, not
  in HTML, not in bundles. Settings endpoints return { configured: boolean } only.
- Secrets at rest: AES-256-GCM via src/server/auth/crypto.ts. Never plaintext files.
- All UI copy in Dutch (jij-vorm); code identifiers in English.
- Reuse the design system (docs/DESIGN_PRINCIPLES.md §3). Second repetition of
  markup = extract a component. Use tokens, not ad-hoc Tailwind colors.
- Tests per docs/TESTING.md; CI never calls live Picnic/Bring/Google/LLM APIs
  (FAKE_AI=1 + fetch mocks). Every bugfix ships a regression test.
- Never commit: .env, /data, real credentials, recorded fixtures containing
  personal data (sanitize recordings).

## Git
- Conventional commits ("feat(plan): ...", "test(shopping): ...").
- No force-push on shared branches. No drive-by refactors outside WP scope.
